{"lemma":"سُراةٌ","slug":"سُراةٌ","root":"س.ر.#","root_slug":"س-ر-_","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ر-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19449","n19450","n19652","n19674"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19449","headword_ar":"سَرْاَةٌ","root":"srA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saro'N","text_ar":"سَرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n19450","headword_ar":"سِرْاَةٌ","root":"srA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saro'N","text_ar":"سَرْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n19652","headword_ar":"سَرَاةٌ","root":"srw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"back"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) of anything: (S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarawaAtN","text_ar":"سَرَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, K:) it has no broken pl. (M.) And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"higher,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"highest, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything: (M in the present art., and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srY","text_ar":"سرى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) so [for instance] of a mountain. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srY","text_ar":"سرى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraApu Alyamani","text_ar":"سَرَاةُ اليَمَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~araApu","text_ar":"السَّرَاةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by way of preeminence, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAp","text_ar":"سَرَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is prefixed to the names of a number of places and of tribes, as is said in the TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srY","text_ar":"سرى"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain mountain"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mountainous tract"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commencing near 'Arafát and extending to Nejrán of El-Yemen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) pl. as above. (M.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"highest"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most advanced state"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of the day: (TA:) [or] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of advancement, when the sun has become somewhat high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotifaAE","text_ar":"اِرْتِفَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of the day, (M, K, TA,) and so of other things; by some said to mean the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof; (M;) so in the S, in relation to the day; but this is [said to be] a mistake: (TA:)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1354},{"kind":"text","text":"in a verse of El-Bureyk El-Hudhalee, of the night: pl. as above: and the sing. also occurs used as a pl. (M.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything: pl. as above. (S.) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle and main part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a road; (Mgh, Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard and elevated part"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (K.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa lilon~isaA='i","text_ar":"لَيْسَ لِلْنِّسَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sarawaAtu AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"سَرَوَاتُ الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The back and middle of the road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the middle and main parts thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are not for the women;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning that they should walk upon the side parts. (S.) ―         -b4-  Accord. to Er-Rághib,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wide tract of land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srY","text_ar":"سرى"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  It is also a pl., of a rare form, (S, Msb,) or a quasi-pl. n., (M, K,) of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sariY~N","text_ar":"سَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see in several places]. (S, M, Msb, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","Msb","TA","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n19674","headword_ar":"سَرَاةٌ","root":"srY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"srw","text_ar":"سرو"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}